    <div class="pyq-insight">
      <strong>What does the cutoff mean?</strong> You need roughly 90-100 marks (45-50%) in a normal year. With negative marking of -0.66, answering 75 questions correctly out of 85 attempted is a safe strategy. The 2023 dip shows that paper difficulty varies — don't panic if the paper feels hard; cutoff adjusts.
    </div>

